{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, by the construction in Lemma 3.2, X vanishes along the identity section.",
    "Notice that X is well-defined only up to adding a global Killing field K, which in the gradient case must be parallel.",
    "We will assume K = 0; the proof for K ̸ = 0 parallel is analogous.",
    "Suppose first that N is abelian.",
    "We may assume without loss of generality that f vanishes along the zero section."
  ]
